WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.166 --> 00:00:04.208
Mr. Kolakušić, the war in Ukraine is soon entering its fifth year.

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:07.666
In your opinion, is there any end to this war in sight?

00:00:09.125 --> 00:00:12.583
The end of the war will come in the way I’ve been saying for years,

00:00:13.041 --> 00:00:16.333
because a major mistake was made at the beginning.

00:00:16.333 --> 00:00:18.916
At the beginning there was an opportunity for peace.

00:00:18.958 --> 00:00:24.458
However, the EU and its leadership chose another path.

00:00:24.750 --> 00:00:30.333
And that other path was: we don’t want peace, Russia must be defeated,

00:00:30.958 --> 00:00:34.958
we’ll impose sanctions on Russia, we want to change Russia’s leadership,

00:00:34.958 --> 00:00:36.625
we want Russia to collapse.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:41.250
Of course, these were childish games, complete nonsense,

00:00:41.750 --> 00:00:45.333
because I said four years ago in the European Parliament,

00:00:45.750 --> 00:00:49.541
sanctions have never changed a single government.

00:00:49.666 --> 00:00:52.750
The greatest sanctions were imposed on North Korea,

00:00:52.750 --> 00:00:56.041
and the same family has ruled for 60, 70 years.

00:00:56.625 --> 00:01:00.291
We also had complete isolation, so to speak,

00:01:00.666 --> 00:01:04.583
of the island of Cuba; Fidel Castro ruled until his death,

00:01:04.583 --> 00:01:09.250
and now the country is run by people who share the exact same views.

00:01:09.541 --> 00:01:12.125
You cannot change a government through sanctions.

00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:15.208
But what have the EU sanctions brought?

00:01:15.333 --> 00:01:19.833
EU sanctions have brought the destruction of the European economy.

00:01:20.125 --> 00:01:22.625
They have brought enormous debt.

00:01:23.291 --> 00:01:27.166
How much has the EU borrowed in the last few years,

00:01:27.166 --> 00:01:30.291
if you told that to economists or prime ministers,

00:01:30.291 --> 00:01:33.750
presidents of EU member states,

00:01:34.208 --> 00:01:37.500
they would all say: such a thing is impossible.

00:01:38.166 --> 00:01:42.458
Hundreds of billions of euros were sent to Ukraine

00:01:42.458 --> 00:01:45.208
and disappeared there; no one knows where they ended up,

00:01:45.208 --> 00:01:48.833
no one is even tracking what’s happening with that money, etc.

00:01:48.833 --> 00:01:53.625
So, Russia will go on to capture everything it set out to capture,

00:01:54.125 --> 00:01:57.875
it will place under its control, so to speak,

00:01:57.916 --> 00:02:01.166
those areas it considers to belong to Russia

00:02:01.166 --> 00:02:03.500
and in which Russians live.

00:02:04.666 --> 00:02:07.791
To think it was possible to defeat Russia

00:02:07.833 --> 00:02:11.791
was simply absolutely foolish,

00:02:12.041 --> 00:02:14.666
because it was based on nothing.

00:02:14.666 --> 00:02:17.333
We now see Ukraine lacking soldiers.

00:02:17.916 --> 00:02:21.541
How can a country of 50 million be lacking soldiers?

00:02:21.541 --> 00:02:25.541
That army should number 2 million people,

00:02:25.541 --> 00:02:28.416
at least—2 million armed men and women.

00:02:28.958 --> 00:02:31.833
So, we all want complete equality.

00:02:31.958 --> 00:02:33.625
A million men, a million women.

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:36.416
So where is the problem, Mr. Zelensky?

00:02:36.916 --> 00:02:40.458
What, in your estimation, will happen when Russia captures

00:02:40.458 --> 00:02:42.250
what it set out in its constitution?

00:02:42.250 --> 00:02:44.083
Will the war be frozen?

00:02:44.083 --> 00:02:50.666
What is the plan—of Russia, but also of the EU and Ukraine—in this regard?

00:02:51.583 --> 00:02:56.250
Well, what we saw in the initial attempts

00:02:56.250 --> 00:03:01.333
to establish peace by the President of the United States,

00:03:01.333 --> 00:03:05.500
Donald Trump, is that Russia in no way

00:03:05.500 --> 00:03:09.583
accepts any peace agreement that would exclude

00:03:09.625 --> 00:03:12.000
the surrender of the entire Donbas to Russia.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:17.208
And now we see that Russia is striking the Donbas with full force

00:03:17.208 --> 00:03:21.500
and will likely conquer it in the coming period

00:03:21.500 --> 00:03:24.625
of several months or a year.

00:03:24.791 --> 00:03:29.791
We also sadly see increased advances in Zaporizhzhia,

00:03:29.791 --> 00:03:34.541
which President Putin said he would even leave

00:03:34.541 --> 00:03:38.666
to Ukraine. But we have the biggest problem:

00:03:38.916 --> 00:03:43.583
even if Russia were to conquer everything, absolutely everything,

00:03:43.916 --> 00:03:47.500
we still have the problem that Ukraine and Zelensky

00:03:47.500 --> 00:03:52.250
do not want to hold elections.

00:03:52.958 --> 00:03:57.333
And the only interest of members of the Ukrainian parliament and Zelensky

00:03:57.333 --> 00:04:02.000
is always—and forever—that the war never ends.

00:04:02.250 --> 00:04:07.916
Because according to their law, not their constitution, they can remain presidents

00:04:07.916 --> 00:04:12.291
and members of parliament, managing hundreds of billions

00:04:12.291 --> 00:04:18.041
coming from the EU and the USA and be, essentially, lifelong rulers,

00:04:18.041 --> 00:04:22.500
so to speak. If the war continues for life, they are in power for life.

00:04:22.500 --> 00:04:26.625
They don’t need any elections. Europe and the whole world accept this.

00:04:26.916 --> 00:04:31.125
Everyone simply accepts it. So we have the danger

00:04:31.416 --> 00:04:37.958
of a perpetual war, even if Russian aggression and attacks were to stop.

00:04:38.416 --> 00:04:41.958
Because Zelensky and the current—I don’t even know what to call it—

00:04:42.166 --> 00:04:47.041
ragtag EU leadership would say: no, no, no, it can’t end like this,

00:04:47.041 --> 00:04:52.166
we must regain all of Ukraine’s territory, even though every being

00:04:52.166 --> 00:04:56.000
with minimal IQ knows this is impossible.

